Good question — since your environment got partially corrupted, you need a full clean removal before reinstalling mirror registry.

I’ll give you a safe + complete cleanup procedure (tested approach for disconnected OCP mirror setups).


---

🚨 FULL MIRROR REGISTRY CLEANUP (COMPLETE RESET)

🔴 1. Stop all mirror-related services

systemctl stop quay-app
systemctl stop quay-pod
systemctl stop redis

Also disable:

systemctl disable quay-app quay-pod redis


---

🔴 2. Remove systemd service files

rm -f /etc/systemd/system/quay-app.service
rm -f /etc/systemd/system/quay-pod.service
rm -f /etc/systemd/system/redis.service

systemctl daemon-reload


---

🔴 3. Remove all podman containers / pods

podman ps -a
podman rm -f $(podman ps -aq) 2>/dev/null

podman pod rm -f $(podman pod ps -aq) 2>/dev/null


---

🔴 4. Reset podman completely (VERY IMPORTANT)

podman system reset -f

👉 This fixes your earlier issue (overlay corruption)


---

🔴 5. Clean container storage (if still needed)

umount -l /var/lib/containers/storage/overlay-containers/*/userdata/shm 2>/dev/null

rm -rf /var/lib/containers/storage
rm -rf /run/containers/storage


---

🔴 6. Remove Quay data directories

rm -rf /root/quay-install
rm -rf /root/quay-rootCA
rm -rf /var/lib/registry


---

🔴 7. Remove mirror registry installation directory

rm -rf ~/mirror

(or wherever you extracted mirror-registry)


---

🔴 8. Remove podman volumes

podman volume rm -f $(podman volume ls -q)


---

🔴 9. Clean SELinux labels (optional but recommended)

restorecon -Rv /root


---

🔴 10. Verify CLEAN state

Run:

podman ps -a
podman images
podman volume ls

👉 All should be empty


---

✅ NOW REINSTALL CLEANLY

🔵 1. Extract mirror-registry again

tar -xvf mirror-registry.tar.gz
cd mirror


---

🔵 2. Ensure required files exist

ls

Must have:

execution-environment.tar

image-archive.tar



---

🔵 3. (Optional but recommended) Disable SELinux temporarily

setenforce 0


---

🔵 4. Install mirror registry

./mirror-registry install \
  --initUser sysadmin \
  --initPassword samsung123 \
  --quayHostname mirror1.cl2-mno1-rvt.lan


---

🚀 AFTER INSTALL VERIFY

podman ps

You should see:

quay-app

redis

quay-pod



---

Then test:

curl -k https://mirror1.cl2-mno1-rvt.lan:8443/health/instance


---

💥 COMMON MISTAKES (YOU HIT BEFORE)

❌ Deleting /var/lib/containers/storage manually
❌ Not loading image archive
❌ SELinux blocking mounts
❌ Partial reinstall without cleanup


